itemDescription: Welsh princess and mistress of Henry II of England

wikipedia_page.main: Nest Bloet (died 1224/5), sometimes called "Nest of Wales", was a Welsh noblewoman, best known for her many romantic liaisons, including an extramarital affair with King Henry II of England. She was the daughter of Angharad, daughter of Uthred Bishop of Llandaff, and Iorwerth ab Owain, the lord of Caerleon.
